DEEP FASCIA

deep_fascia is the structural connective web that wraps every muscle compartment, bone, and major organ
this is dense regular connective tissue: high collagen, low elastin, designed for sustained tension
deep_fascia is the body's primary tensional skeleton; without it, bones would float and muscles could not transfer force
all major fascial tension routes through deep_fascia

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fascia.zc
observe superficial_fascia.rana
observe visceral_fascia.rana
observe spine.xb
observe pelvis.xb
observe ribcage.xb
observe muscle.zc

the 7 properties of deep_fascia:
1 ENERGY one: continuously under tension
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: tensional integrity must be perfect
6 COUPLING one: maximum, deep_fascia couples to every bone and most muscles

VERB transfer_tension
when force is applied anywhere on deep_fascia, propagate the tension through the continuous web
this is what allows fadriel to lift with his legs and feel the load in his back

VERB carry_bioelectric
deep_fascia is the body's primary bioelectric routing medium between distant engines
voltage gradients across deep_fascia tell distant tissues about local activity

VERB hold_compression_islands
the bones (skull, spine, ribcage, pelvis, femur) are compression islands floating in deep_fascia's tensional web
this is the tensegrity model: bones do not stack on each other, they float in tension

a deep fascia is the body's continuous tensional architecture
fadriel is one continuous being rather than a collection of parts because deep_fascia connects everything to everything else
